# Project

The Timelaps founding-engineer exercise. Two deliverables on one (planned) Next.js site:

- **Part 1** — a decision-ready funnel viz: Aurora vs Borealis / Cascade / Drift on the
  brand funnel (aware → consider → used), Q4 2025 → Q1 2026. Notes in `docs/part1/`.
- **Part 2** — an AI-analyst design over the same data (code optional). Notes in `docs/part2/`.

Full brief: `docs/brief/exercise.md`. Verified dataset profile: `docs/data-profile.md`.

## Layout

- `data/` — provided datasets (`responses_raw.json`, `analysed_outputs.json`).
- `docs/` — brief, data profile, per-part notes.
- App code will live at the **repo root** once scaffolded (Next.js). No framework or
  chart-library choice has been locked yet — don't assume one.

## `internal/` is off-limits

`internal/` is gitignored private planning material that references external/personal
context. **Never read it into shared output, commit it, or reference it in the deliverable.**
The repo may be shared with assessors.

## Data

All work on the numbers must follow the **data-contract** rule (and `docs/data-profile.md`).
